# Icons: Phosphor only

## Required

- **All UI icons** must come from `@phosphor-icons/react`.
- Import named icons from `@phosphor-icons/react` (e.g. `House`, `Plus`, `ArrowLeft`).
- Default to `weight="light"` unless the surrounding screen already uses a different weight consistently.
- For **category visuals**, use the existing `CategoryIcon` component — it maps categories to Phosphor icons.

```tsx
import { House } from '@phosphor-icons/react';

<House size={20} weight="light" color="#1A1A2E" />
```

## Forbidden — never use these as icons

- **Unicode emoji** in UI: `🏠`, `🛒`, `📱`, strings from `category.emoji`, or any emoji in buttons, tabs, charts, lists, empty states, or labels.
- **WhatsApp / iMessage / sticker-style illustrated icons** — colorful flat illustrations, 3D emoji, Apple emoji art, Twemoji, Noto Emoji, OpenMoji, or similar used as interface icons.
- **Other icon libraries** for app UI: `lucide-react`, `@mui/icons-material`, `react-icons`, Heroicons, Font Awesome, Tabler, etc.
- **`<img>` / SVG assets** used as generic UI icons when a Phosphor equivalent exists (logos and user-uploaded avatars are fine).
- **Inline SVG icon copies** pasted from design kits unless there is no Phosphor equivalent and the user explicitly asked for a custom asset.

If you find emoji or Lucide in code you are editing, **replace them with Phosphor** in the same change.

## Phosphor naming

- Browse: https://phosphoricons.com
- Use PascalCase component names (`Trash`, `Gear`, `ChartBar`), not string icon names.

## Exceptions (only these)

- **Brand logos** (Google, Apple sign-in) where an official logo asset is required.
- **User avatars** (uploaded photos or crop UI).

## Checklist before finishing

- [ ] No `lucide-react` imports anywhere under `src/`.
- [ ] No emoji characters used as icons in JSX or chart axes.
- [ ] Category rows use `<CategoryIcon categoryId={...} />`, not emoji text.
